# No-Route Sort Workflow — 7 Stories

Summary of each story as a flowchart for reviewing business logic.

---

## Story 1 — No-Route Discovery & Collection

**Description:** Shipment enters sort, no route found → system creates tasks, worker collects into container.

**Actors:** Carlos (Induction Worker) · Ana (Sort Worker) · Conductor (System)

### Flow

```
Carlos: Scan shipment at induction
  → Routing System: No route found
  → Conductor: Print NO-ROUTE label [Workflow begins]
  → Create 2 Tasks: Collection Task + Routing Task
  → Carlos: Apply label, push onto belt [No change to rhythm]
  → Ana (Sort Floor): Scan shipment from belt
  → App: "No route. Collect to container"
  → Ana: Go to no-route cart, scan cart barcode
  → Ana: Place shipment into cart
  → Conductor: Validate container [Confirm placement]
  → ✅ Collection Task COMPLETE [Routing Task still OPEN]
```

### Tasks

| Task | Description | Proof |
|---|---|---|
| 📦 Collection Task | Worker must collect shipment into no-route container | Scan shipment + scan container |
| 🗺️ Routing Task | Shipment needs to be assigned a route — handled by routing team outside Conductor | Routing event from external system |

> 💡 **Key insight:** Carlos and Ana do exactly what they always do — scan, label, place. The system records physical proof through scans. No added cognitive load.

