## Story 2 — Routing Observed & Re-Sort

**Description:** Routing team assigns routes to no-route shipments → Conductor observes → creates re-sort tasks → workers re-sort.

**Actors:** Ray (Supervisor) · Tech Support (External) · Marco (Runner) · Carlos / Ana · Conductor

### Flow

```
Ray: Sees 47 open routing tasks → Contacts Tech Support
  → Tech Support: Routes 42/47 shipments [In external routing system]
  → Conductor observes: Receives routing events for 42 shipments
  → Per shipment: Routing Task → DONE | Re-sort Task → CREATED
  → Ray: Directs Marco to bring pallet to induction
  → Marco: Uses pallet jack, moves pallet to induction
  → Marco: Scan pallet QR → "Move to induction"
  → Conductor: Pallet marked as consumed by sort session
```

**Carlos scans each shipment off pallet:**

| ✅ Route assigned | ❌ Still no route |
|---|---|
| Print route label | Print no-route label |
| Push onto belt | Push onto belt (as normal) |
| Ana: Scan → Sort to correct position | Ana: Re-collect into new container |
| ✅ Re-sort Task DONE — Workflow COMPLETE | Routing Task still OPEN — Awaiting routing |

> 💡 **Key insight:** Conductor *observes* routing events from external system — it does not route itself. Each routing event automatically completes the Routing Task and creates a new Re-sort Task.

