## Story 5 — Route Reversal

**Description:** Shipment already re-sorted → routing team removes route → workflow "re-opens" → new tasks created to retrieve shipment.

**Actors:** Tech Support (External) · Ray (Supervisor) · Marco (Runner) · Conductor

### Flow

```
SHP-45033: Re-sort complete — workflow DONE
  → Tech Support: Restructure route → SHP-45033 removed from route
  → Conductor observes: Route removal event
  → Conductor: Workflow "re-opens" [Shipment is at wrong position]
  → Create: 🗺️ New Routing Task (needs new route)
           + 📦 New Collection Task (must retrieve from position B-8)

⚠️ SHP-45033 is still at position B-8 — if not collected, it may be loaded onto the wrong vehicle.
   This is why the Collection Task is mandatory.

  → Ray: Dashboard alert — route-reversed shipment → Directs Marco to B-8
  → Marco: Go to B-8, scan SHP-45033
  → Marco: Scan no-route container
  → Conductor: Collection Task DONE [Routing Task still OPEN]
  → SHP-45033 re-enters normal no-route cycle [Awaiting routing → re-sort / defer / RTS]
```

> 💡 **Key insight:** A "done" workflow can be reopened by an external event. Conductor observes continuously — not only at workflow creation. Route reversal is the only event type that re-opens a completed workflow.

