## Story 6 — Ray's Dashboard: Directing the Operation

**Description:** Ray sees the full session picture, coordinates the team based on dashboard — every shipment has a clear state, nothing gets lost.

**Actors:** Ray (Supervisor) · Conductor Dashboard

### Dashboard at 7:30 PM (90 min into session)

| State | Count | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| Collected | 46 / 47 | In no-route container, confirmed by scan |
| Awaiting Routing | 12 | No route yet, waiting on tech support |
| Routed — Pending Re-sort | 6 | Route assigned, pallet not yet at induction |
| Re-sorted ✅ | 28 | Workflow complete |
| Route Reversed | 1 | SHP-45033 — collected back, awaiting new route |

### Decisions Ray makes based on dashboard

```
Ray @ 7:30 PM: 6 routed — pending re-sort → Marco brings pallet to induction
  (independently)
Ray @ 7:30 PM: 12 unrouted, 90 min remaining → Tech Support prioritises routing 12 shipments
  ↓ @ 8:45 PM
Ray: 5 still unrouted → Defer → Storage Task
  (simultaneously)
Ray: 1 recurring problem → Initiate RTS
```

### 9:00 PM — Session end state

| Outcome | Count |
|---|---|
| Re-sorted ✅ | 40 |
| Deferred to storage 🏪 | 5 |
| RTS 📤 | 1 |
| Late-routed & re-sorted ✅ | 1 |

**→ 0 shipments forgotten. Every obligation proven.**

